    "causal_summary": "A cross-skill audit of the deep skill family (`deep-research`, `deep-review`, `deep-context`, `deep-ai-council`, `deep-improvement`) against the `deep-loop-runtime` feature catalogue revealed three exploitable gaps: `deep-improvement` used hand-rolled, non-atomic JSONL writes with a silent-drop pattern; `deep-review` had no loop-lock, enabling a concurrent-run race; and `deep-context`'s executor-audit env was prose-only. Three targeted fixes closed these gaps. Five deliberate non-fixes (judged over-engineering after a cli-opencode architect consult and two independent confidence-gate audits) are recorded in `decision-record.md` as accepted ADRs.",
